# jet.obj — a simple low-poly placeholder aircraft.
# The .obj format is plain text: "v x y z" defines a vertex, and "f a b c"
# defines a triangular face from three vertices (numbered from 1).
# This model faces -Z (forward) with +Y up, matching the engine's convention.
# Replace it with a real .obj or .glb via the Model component's Browse button.
o Jet

# --- vertices ---
v  0.00  0.00 -2.00   # 1 nose
v -0.35 -0.10  1.00   # 2 body back-left
v  0.35 -0.10  1.00   # 3 body back-right
v  0.00  0.30  0.20   # 4 canopy top
v -1.80  0.00  0.60   # 5 left wingtip
v  1.80  0.00  0.60   # 6 right wingtip
v  0.00  0.00  1.40   # 7 tail back
v  0.00  0.75  1.20   # 8 fin top

# --- body ---
f 1 4 2
f 1 3 4
f 1 2 3
f 2 4 3
f 2 3 7
f 2 7 4
f 4 7 3

# --- wings (listed both ways so each is visible from above and below) ---
f 1 5 2
f 1 2 5
f 1 3 6
f 1 6 3

# --- tail fin (both ways too) ---
f 4 8 7
f 4 7 8
